### Backoffice Demo API — ejemplos de peticiones
### Compatible con la extensión "REST Client" de VS Code o IntelliJ HTTP client.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Login (admin) — copia el token de la respuesta
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Guarda el token de la respuesta anterior
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 2. Listar productos (paginado + filtros)
GET {{host}}/api/products?page=0&size=10&sort=price,desc&category=Electrónica
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Buscar por nombre o SKU
GET {{host}}/api/products?search=SKU-0001
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Dashboard (agregados)
GET {{host}}/api/products/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Crear producto (solo ADMIN)
POST {{host}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "DEMO-100",
  "name": "Producto de prueba",
  "category": "Oficina",
  "price": 149.95,
  "stock": 30,
  "active": true
}

### 6. Actualizar producto
PUT {{host}}/api/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "DEMO-100",
  "name": "Producto actualizado",
  "category": "Oficina",
  "price": 159.95,
  "stock": 25,
  "active": true
}

### 7. Eliminar producto
DELETE {{host}}/api/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
